These Root Macros are free for anyone to use and improve.  
You are encouraged to add your own root macros - even if
they are not "generically implimented." They may still
provide a good example to others.


To get a copy of these macros:

  cvs co UserCode/RootMacros


To add your own macro:

  cvs co UserCode/RootMacros
  cd UserCode/RootMacros/
  cp /path/to/your/macro.C .
  cvs add macro.C
  cvs commit -m "This macro does X" macro.C


To improve a macro:

  cvs co UserCode/RootMacros
  cd UserCode/RootMacros/
    [edit a macro]
  cvs commit -m "Added new feature X" macro.C



Mike Anderson, Sept 8, 2008
